<h2>Join</h2>
<p>
    A JOIN clause is used to combine rows from two or more tables, based on a related column between them.
    Let's focus on LEFT OUTER JOIN
</p>
<h2>Left JOIN</h2>
<p>
    The LEFT OUTER JOIN keyword returns all records from the left table (table1),
    and the matching records from the right table (table2).
    The result is 0 records from the right side, if there is no match.
</p>
<pre>
SELECT column_name(s)
FROM table1
LEFT OUTER JOIN table2
ON table1.column_name = table2.column_name;
</pre>
<div class="message message-hint">
    In MySQL the LEFT Keyword is optional.
</div>

