<h3>Attention</h3>
<p>
    If you want to filter the left table, you have to check if it is NULL or the desired value.
    If the NULL comparison is forgotten, the JOIN behaves like an INNER JOIN
</p>
<p>
    It's also possible to add the filter condition to the ON JOIN Condition instead of the where condition.
</p>

<h4>Comparison</h4>
<pre>
SELECT column_name
    FROM table_one
    LEFT JOIN table_two ON table_one.key = table_two.key
    WHERE (table_two.VALUE IS NULL OR table_two.VALUE = 'foobar')
</pre>
VS.
<pre>
    SELECT column_name
    FROM table_one
    LEFT JOIN table_two ON table_one.key = table_two.key
            AND table_two.VALUE = 'foobar'
</pre>